            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine sanctae et individuae Trinitatis. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> gratia Dei
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Quia pauperibus et orfanis temporale
                        subsidium conferre omnimodis convenit, idcirco omnium fidelium sanctae Dei
                        Aecclesiae nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum industria
                        comperiat, <persName key="#Intercessory #vassusOf" ref="#people/601"
                            >Hegilricum</persName> illustrem <rs key="#vassusOf">vassum nostrum</rs>
                        qui et Azo vocatur suppliciter nostram exorasse <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >clementiam</rs>, quatenus <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >tres ariales</rs>, sitos in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs> Athesi,
                        pertinentes de <geogName key="#Viscount" ref="#estates/124"><placeName
                                key="#Viscount" ref="#places/59"><rs key="#Viscount"
                                    >vicecomitatu</rs> Veronensi</placeName></geogName>, a<rs
                            key="#Bridges/pontoons"> ponte scilicet Fracto</rs> usque ad <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >arialem</rs> illum quem <persName key="#Deacons"><name
                                ref="Petreuertus">Pedreverto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diacono </rs>per <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            >precepti paginam </rs>contulimus existentes, nec non et quosdam <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave #siblingOf">servos germanos iuris regni nostri
                            </rs><persName key="#Royal_slave #siblingOf"><name ref="Walterius"
                                >Vualtari </name></persName>videlicet et <persName
                            key="#Royal_slave #siblingOf"><name ref="Lupus"
                            >Luponem</name></persName> una cum <rs key="#Royal_slave #motherOf"
                            >matre</rs> sua nomine <persName key="#Royal_slave #motherOf"><name
                                ref="Lupa">Lupula</name></persName>, pertinentes <geogName
                            key="#Sculdahis #Other_administrative_unit #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#estates/182"><placeName
                                key="#Sculdahis #Other_administrative_unit #Royal_slave">de quadam
                                    <rs key="#Sculdahis #Other_administrative_unit">sculdassia
                                </rs>que Fluvium</placeName> nominatur</geogName>, per hoc regale
                        preceptum cuidam <rs key="#Priests #fidelisOf">clerico fideli nostro</rs>
                        nomine <persName key="#Priests" ref="#people/1501">Iohanni </persName><rs
                            key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">iure proprietario</rs> concedere pro
                        Dei amore et remedio animae nostrae atque largiri modis omnibus usque im
                        perpetuum dignaremur. Cuius precibus libenter acclinati predictos tres
                        ariales infra prescripta confinia in iam dicto fluvio Athesi consistentes,
                        prout priscis temporibus nostrae regiae parti ex integro pertinuerunt, seu
                        et iam fatos servos simul cum matre illorum de preltaxata sculdassia
                        pertinentes cum filiis et filiabus illorum sive quicquid in presenti habere
                        et in posterum acquire potuerint, hac nostra regali inscriptione eidem
                        Iohanni clerico concedimus et largimur, ac de nostro iure et dominio in eius
                        ius et dominium in integrum transfundimus atque donamus, ut habeat, teneat,
                        possideat faciatque in omnibus quicquid eius decreverit animus vel voluntas,
                        potestatemque habeat donandi, vendendi, alienandi, commutandi seu quicquid
                        voluerit faciendi, absque totius potestatis contradictione. Si quis hoc
                        nostrae concessionis preceptum quolibet ingenio infringere aut aliquo modo
                        violare quesierit, ut conatus eius irritus habeatur, <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >centum libras auri optimi</rs> solvere cogatur, medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camerae nostrae</rs> et medietatem prefato Iohanni
                            <rs key="#Priests">clerico </rs>suisque heredibus. Quod ut verius
                        credatur et diligentius observetur, manu propria roborantes de anulo nostro
                        assignari precepimus. Signum domni (MF) Berengarii serenissimi regis.
                            <persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/619">Ambrosius </persName><rs
                            key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi </persName><rs
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">episcopi et archicancellarii</rs>
                        recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SI D) Data kal. aug., anno dominice
                        incarnationis .DCCCCV., d[om]ni vero Berengari serenissimi regis .XVIII.,
                        indictione .VIII. Actum <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention" ref="#places/364"
                                ><rs key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            >Tulles</rs></placeName>. in Christi nomine feliciter, amen. </ab>
